name: adal
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "adal" %}
{% set version = "1.2.7" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: d74f45b81317454d96e982fd1c50e6fb5c99ac2223728aea8764433a39f566f1

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
  run:
    - cryptography >=1.1.0
    - pyjwt >=1.0.0
    - python >=3.6
    - python-dateutil >=2.1.0
    - requests >=2.0.0

test:
  imports:
    - adal
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/AzureAD/azure-activedirectory-library-for-python
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: |
    The ADAL for Python library makes it easy for python application to authenticate 
    to Azure Active Directory (AAD) in order to access AAD protected web resources.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - marcelotrevisani
